reinvent%20and%20discard%20what%20we've%20created%3B%20that's%20happening%20now%20as%20we%20adapt%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20that%20has%20helped%20us%20grow.%20Today%2C%20ShipperHQ%20is%20based%20in%20Austin%2C%20where%20we%20have%2047%20employees.%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20did%20about%20%2415%20million%20in%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c72531fa-374a-488b-b8d0-3e5c3913cafd%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20fit%20the%20mold%20of%20a%20tech%20CEO%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20think%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-ceos-weigh-in-openai-chief-sam-altman-leadership-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20tech%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20in%20Austin%2C%20they%20don't%20picture%20me.%20I'm%20a%2053-year-old%20mom.%20My%20working-class%20English%20accent%20sounds%20more%20like%20the%201980s%20gangsta%20film%20%26quot%3BLock%2C%20Stock%20and%20Two%20Smoking%20Barrels%26quot%3B%20than%20%26quot%3BDownton%20Abbey.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20I've%20become%20sick%20of%20justifying%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20don't%20fit%20the%20mold.%20I%20want%20to%20show%20that%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20look%20or%20sound%20how%20people%20expect.%20The%20success%20of%20my%20company%20speaks%20for%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229aa76278-52da-4375-bda7-e9f4b2e5e5cf%5C%22%3EMy%20past%20traumas%20left%20me%20searching%20for%20security%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20been%20chasing%20a%20feeling%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-money-advice-no-one-wants-to-hear-spend-less-than-earned-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20security%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20mom%20died%20from%20cancer%20when%20I%20was%2022.%20After%20that%2C%20I%20went%20into%20debt%20and%20had%20to%20scramble%20just%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrieved-mother-death-quality-time-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMy%20mom's%20death%20still%20impacts%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%2030%20years%20later.%20I%20assumed%20I'd%20be%20dead%20by%2050%2C%20like%20her.%20Because%20of%20that%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20stability%20for%20my%20sons.%20If%20I%20died%2C%20I%20wanted%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stand%20on%20their%20own%20two%20feet%20without%20me.%20That's%20what%20drove%20me%20as%20a%20business%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20I%20felt%20financially%20safe%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20The%20pandemic%20increased%20the%20business%20revenue.%20More%20importantly%2C%20I%20started%20to%20truly%20trust%20myself.%20It%20took%20only%2012%20years%2C%20but%20I%20have%20finally%20come%20to%20believe%20in%20the%20decision%20I%20made%20as%20a%20business%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20safety%20gave%20me%20the%20confidence%20to%20enjoy%20life%20now%2C%20without%20the%20constant%20scramble%20for%20growth.%20I%20didn't%20want%20my%20teenage%20sons%20to%20move%20out%20without%20feeling%20like%20I'd%20really%20enjoyed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e21546b7-88ca-44e1-809f-5075d244d33b%5C%22%3EI%20want%20my%20sons%20to%20have%20more%20than%20I%20did%2C%20but%20not%20too%20much%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20wanted%20my%20kids%20to%20have%20more%20than%20I%20had%2C%20I%20was%20also%20very%20afraid%20of%20destroying%20them%20by%20giving%20them%20too%20much.%20I%20believe%20money%20is%20a%20very%20powerful%20and%20potentially%20dangerous%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftherapist-ultra-rich-high-net-worth-earn-30-million-problems-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewealth%20counselor%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20She%20has%20helped%20the%20entire%20family%20process%20their%20feelings%20about%20wealth.%20She's%20become%20like%20a%20grandmother%20to%20my%20kids%20and%20has%20helped%20us%20reframe%20our%20thoughts.%20There's%20a%20lot%20to%20unwrap%20there%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20personal.%20However%2C