20Around%20that%20time%2C%20I%20was%20also%20taking%20entrepreneurship%20classes.%20I%20found%20myself%20drawn%20just%20as%20much%20to%20balance%20sheets%20and%20business%20models%20as%20I%20was%20to%20anatomy%20charts%2C%20and%20began%20thinking%20of%20building%20something%20of%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20after%20a%20job%20interview%20left%20me%20feeling%20like%20I'd%20be%20selling%20my%20soul%20to%20a%20defense%20contractor%2C%20I%20called%20my%20wife%20and%20told%20her%20I%20was%20either%20going%20to%20start%20a%20company%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-a-medal-of-honor-marine-reenlisted-years-after-leaving-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20the%20military%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20didn't%20miss%20a%20beat%20and%20asked%20me%20what%20kind%20of%20company%20we'd%20be%20starting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%20KC%20Cattle%20Company%20was%20born%20%E2%80%94%20an%20idea%20rooted%20in%20my%20twin%20passions%20for%20animals%20and%20business%2C%20even%20though%20I%20had%20almost%20zero%20ranching%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cd7a462-afc6-4f47-8ce6-82f2a218ce0e%5C%22%3ELearning%20the%20hard%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20the%20next%20few%20years%20making%20what%20I%20called%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Btuition%20payments%20at%20the%20school%20of%20hard%20knocks%26quot%3B%20while%20I%20figured%20things%20out%20the%20hard%20way.%20I%20interned%20at%20vet%20clinics%2C%20worked%20on%20research%20farms%2C%20and%20learned%20from%20anyone%20who%20would%20let%20me%20tag%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20I%20bought%20420%20acres%20of%20land%20about%2045%20minutes%20northwest%20of%20Kansas%20City%20and%20started%20raising%20a%20few%20dozen%20head%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20cattle.%20Now%20we%20run%20about%20200%20animals%20on%20the%20ranch%2C%20with%20partnerships%20across%20the%20country%2C%20many%20of%20them%20with%20fellow%20veterans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20know%20much%20about%20wagyu%20beyond%20that%20it%20was%20premium%20beef%20with%20an%20incredible%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-from-japan-3d-printed-a-hunk-of-wagyu-beef-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emarbling%20score%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Japanese%20use%20a%20grading%20scale%20from%201%20to%2012%2C%20where%20US%20%26quot%3Bprime%26quot%3B%20beef%20barely%20hits%20a%204.%20Our%20average%20wagyu%20now%20ranks%20around%207%2C%20with%20some%20cuts%20scoring%20as%20high%20as%2010.%20It's%20beef%20that%20genuinely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcooking-wagyu-steak-wrong-way-best-results-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emelts%20in%20your%20mouth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWagyu%20cattle%20are%20expensive%20to%20buy%2C%20feed%2C%20and%20raise.%20They%20take%20longer%20to%20mature%20and%20yield%20less%20beef%20than%20other%20breeds.%20Still%2C%20I%20believed%20that%20if%20we%20were%20going%20to%20charge%20a%20premium%2C%20we%20had%20to%20produce%20the%20best%20beef%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20and%20treat%20our%20animals%20right%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20happy%20cow%20makes%20better%20beef.%20That's%20something%20you%20can%20see%20in%20the%20way%20they%20behave.%20When%20our%20cattle%20are%20lying%20down%20and%20chewing%20their%20cud%2C%20it's%20a%20sign%20they're%20content%20and%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20use%20cattle%20prods%20or%20horses%20to%20move%20them%20%E2%80%94%20anything%20that%20adds%20stress%20hurts%20both%20the%20animal%20and%20the%20final%20product.%20Our%20approach%20isn't%20as%20rigid%20as%20Japan's%2C%20but%20it's%20far%20superior%20to%20most%20traditional%20American%20practices.%20The%20result%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-never-order-at-steakhouse-what-to-get%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigh-quality%20beef%3C%2Fa%3E%20raised%20ethically%2C%20with%20respect%20for%20the%20animal%20and%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249d59b28-0afb-4ce0-9d29-01903bfd44d3%5C%22%3EGoing%20viral%20%E2%80%94%20and%20being%20unprepared%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202018%2C%20I'd%20shifted%20our%20focus%20from%20restaurant%20sales%20to%20e-commerce.%20I%20thought%20online%20retail%20might%20help%20us%20reach%20more%20customers%2C%20but%20we%20struggled%20to%20stand%20out%20%E2%80%94%20until%20one%20day%2C%20everything%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%26quot%3BFood%20%26amp%3B%20Wine%26quot%3B%20named%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhot-dogs-trend-fashion-design-explained-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewagyu%20hot%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20best%20in%20the%20world%20in%202019%2C%20we%20went%20from%20shipping%2020%20orders%20a%20week%20to%2012%2C000%20overnight.%20We%20were%20completely%20overwhelmed.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20I%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20now%20we%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20keep%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20pandemic%20hit.%20When%20major%20meatpackers%20shut%20down%20and%20grocery%20store%20shelves%20emptied%2C%20our%20small%20operation%20suddenly%20became%20a%20lifeline%20for%20people%20looking%20to%20buy%20high-quality%20beef%20directly%20from%20the%20source.%20KC%20Cattle%20Company%20exploded%20in%20popularity%2C%20and%20for%20two%20years%2C%20business%20was%20booming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20pandemic%20subsided%20%E2%80%94%20and%20inflation%20hit%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20shifted%20again.%20Feed%20prices%20spiked.%20Fuel%20costs%20climbed.%20Consumers%20began%20to%20pull%20back%20on%20premium%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20while%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20we%20went%20from%20being%20a%20pandemic%20success%20story%20to%20fighting%20just%20to%20survive.%20But%20that's%20where%20my%20Ranger%20mindset%20kicked%20in%3A%20You%20don't%20quit%20%E2%80%94%20you%20adapt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20that%20pressure%20came%20my%20sec