ary%22%3A%22Some%20of%20Marriott's%20guests%20say%20they%20were%20were%20blindsided%20by%20the%20Sonder%20termination%2C%20with%20one%20being%20told%20to%20vacate%20the%20room%20halfway%20through%20his%20stay.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abharade%40insider.com%20(Aditi%20Bharade)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriott-sonder-licensing-termination-guest-apartment-new-booking-how-2025-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20wife%20and%20I%20pay%20%241%2C200%20a%20month%20for%20a%20house%20manager.%20Buying%20back%20my%20time%2C%20peace%2C%20and%20energy%20is%20more%20valuable%20than%20money.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20family%20of%20three%20on%20a%20park%20bench%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e3e397f37aa653f55a46c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEric%20Roberge%20and%20his%20family.%3Cp%3EBeyond%20Your%20Hammock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEric%20Roberge%20hired%20a%20house%20manager%20to%20work%2010%20hours%20a%20week%20at%20%2428%20an%20hour%20in%20August.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOutsourcing%20household%20chores%20allowed%20him%20and%20his%20wife%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20daughter%20and%20their%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvesting%20in%20help%20increased%20their%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20highlighted%20time%20as%20a%20key%20measure%20of%20wealth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20money%20well%20is%20a%20skill.%20Having%20this%20skill%20means%20knowing%20how%20to%20invest%20wisely%20and%20maintain%20a%20strong%20savings%20habit%2C%20but%20it%20also%20means%20you%20understand%20how%20to%20spend%20money%20with%20intention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20ways%20to%20spend%20well%20is%20to%20buy%20back%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20my%20family%20did%20when%20we%20decided%20to%20hire%20a%20house%20manager.%20Our%20top%20priority%20is%20having%20more%20time%20and%20energy%20to%20be%20fully%20present%20with%20our%204-year-old%20daughter.%20We%20also%20wanted%20to%20devote%20more%20time%20to%20our%20financial%20planning%20business%2C%20which%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20run%20together%2C%20rather%20than%20managing%20our%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20we%20accomplished%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3b00ba7-74dd-460f-93a8-9d70404a1c86%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOutsourcing%20housework%20is%20a%20high-impact%2C%20low-cost%20way%20to%20enjoy%20more%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbeyondyourhammock.com%2Ffinancial-planning-process%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20the%20business%20I%20founded%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20that%20it%20didn't%20rely%20solely%20on%20me%20to%20operate%20was%20the%20best%20way%20to%20reclaim%20my%20time.%20If%20I%20wasn't%20working%20in%20the%20past%2C%20neither%20was%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20now%20have%20a%20larger%20team%2C%20and%20I've%20established%20strict%20working%20hours%20limits.%20I%20also%20have%20a%20greater%20degree%20of%20freedom%20and%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20eat%20breakfast%20and%20dinner%20with%20my%20family%20every%20day%20because%20I'm%20actually%20home%20to%20do%20that%2C%20and%20I%20take%20random%20Monday%20afternoons%20off%20to%20take%20my%20daughter%20to%20events%20or%20the%20playground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20looked%20at%20how%20we%20could%20buy%20back%20my%20wife's%20time%2C%20we%20first%20considered%20hiring%20someone%20in%20the%20business%20to%20take%20on%20some%20of%20her%20workplace%20responsibilities.%20We%20realized%20two%20things%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20would%20take%20meaningful%20work%20she%20loved%20away%20from%20her%20while%20leaving%20other%20tasks%20she%20didn't%2C%20like%20laundry%20and%20household%20errands%2C%20still%20on%20her%20plate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20was%20more%20cost-effective%20to%20outsource%20household%20chores%20that%20took%20time%20away%20from%20not%20just%20her%20workday%2C%20but%20also%20time%20she%20wanted%20to%20spend%20with%20our%20daughter.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d405a6f2-483a-421d-9901-1d006c9e3c52%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20weighed%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20grew%20up%20in%20working-class%20families%3B%20my%20mother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-started-million-dollar-business-nurse-rekmed-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewas%20a%20nurse%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%2040%20years%2C%20and%20my%20wife's%20father%20was%20a%20firefighter%20for%2030.%20The%20idea%20of%20having%20%26quot%3Bhousehold%20help%26quot%3B%20was%20extremely%20foreign%20to%20us.%20Honestly%2C%20it%20felt%20somewhat%20embarrassing%2C%20too.%20Everyone%20else%20could%20%26quot%3Bdo%20it%20all%3B%26quot%3B%20why%20couldn't%20we%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20know%20that%20many%20people%20who%20%26quot%3Bdo%20it%20all%26quot%3B%20aren't%20very%20happy.%20Reports%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fburnout-vs-depression%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eburnout%20and%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20at%20extreme%20highs.%20Mothers%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20often%20extremely%20overwhelmed%20and%20overloaded%2C%20still%20shouldering%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20housework%2C%20even%20in%20dual-income%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20own%20numbers%20%E2%80%94%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20where%20our%20hours%20went%20versus%20where%20we%20wanted%20them%20to%20go%2C%20and%20how%20much%20it%20would%20cost%20to%20change%20that%20%E2%80%94%20didn't%20lie.%20They%20indicated%20we%20needed%20help%20around%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e10388ae-4c09-47ab-8364-431408ab9924%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20we%20hired%20our%20house%20manager%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20by%20creating%20a%20list%20of%20everything%20we%20felt%20we%20could%20%26quot%3Bshed%26quot%3B%20from%20our%20household%20responsibilities.%20We%20used%20that%20list%20to%20create%20the%20following%20job%20description%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe're%20seeking%20a%20part-time%20house%20manager%2Ffamily%20assistant%20with%20light%20nanny%20responsibilities%20for%20our%20family%20of%20three.%20Schedule%20is%20flexible%20and%20can%20be%20built%20around%20your%20preferences.%20Our%20ideal%20candidate%20is%20willing%20to%20assist%20with%20light%20housework%2C%20including%20laundry%20and%20meal%20preparation%2C%20and%20would%20be%20open%20to%20helping%20with%20our%20two%20cats%20as%20well.%20We%20expect%20the%20role%20to%20start%20at%2010%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20but%20there%20is%20room%20to%20expand%20it.%20%2425-%2430%20per%20hour%2C%20dependent%20on%20experience.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20are%20looking%20for%20someone%20who%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EAppreciates%20autonomy%20and%20enjoys%20having%20control%20over%20their%20schedule%2C%20and%20doesn't%20need%20constant%20direction%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EIs%20a%20self-starter%20and%20can%20take%20charge%20of%20their%20own%20projects%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EIs%20interested%20in%20and%20passionate%20about%20kids%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EHas%20a%20willingness%20to%20learn%20our%20family's%20routines%20and%20preferences%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EIs%20curious%2C%20energetic%2C%20and%20compassionate%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20with%20young%20children%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EResponsibilities%20and%20tasks%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EMeal%20prep%2Fhelp%20with%20cooking%2Fgrocery%20pickup%2Fpreschooler%20lunch%20and%20snack%20prep%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3ELaundry%20(one%20load%20of%20towels%2C%20two%20sets%20of%20sheets%2C%20one%20load%20of%20kids'%20laundry%20a%20week)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EBasic%20errands%20like%20mailing%20a%20package%20at%20the%20post%20office%2C%20returning%20items%20to%20the%20store%2C%20returning%20library%20books%2C%20taking%20the%20car%20in%20for%20a%20maintenance%20appointment%2C%20running%20to%20the%20store%20to%20grab%20paper%20towels%2C%20etc%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3ELight%20cleaning%20(wipe%20down%20counters%2C%20sweep%20or%20vacuum%20as%20needed%2C%20put%20away%20clean%20dishes%20as%20needed)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EHelping%20with%20appointments%20(i.e.%2C%20be%20at%20the%20home%20to%20let%20scheduled%20maintenance%20in)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EHome%20organization%2Fdecluttering%20projects%20(reorganizing%20a%20messy%20closet%20on%20occasion%2C%20helping%20put%20up%20or%20take%20down%20seasonal%20decorations%2C%20etc.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EHelp%20with%20cat%20care%20(brushing%20our%20two%20cats%2C%20helping%20take%20both%20to%20the%20vet%2C%20spending%20~15%20minutes%2Fday%20playing%20with%20them)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20had%20our%20description%2C%20we%20posted%20it%20in%20local%20parents'%20and%20moms'%20groups%20on%20Facebook.%20We%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20better%20to%20find%20someone%20familiar%20in%20our%20community%20than%20a%20stranger%20from%20somewhere%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D42703f262688593c8f25d4c5b7b7d788e833d005aa74c4db5aa9bf62ac73e0c9%26postID%3D690e31ea990693f953bcf4c8%26postSlug%3Dhired-house-manager-1200-month-worth-it-2025-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fcare.com%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECare.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20received%20eight%20applications%20and%20hired%20our%20current%20house%20manager%20for%20%2428%20per%20hour%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaunched-career-after-decades-as-a-sahm-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estay-at-home%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E%20whose%20own%20kids%20reached%20elementary%20school%2C%20so%20she%20had%20more%20time%20in%20her%20day%20and%20genuinely%20loved%20the%20work%20we%20needed%20help%20doing.%20We%20pay%20her%20about%20%241%2C200%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20haven't%20really%20been%20any%20downsides.%20The%20only%20thing%20is%20I%20try%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20kitchen%20when%20she's%20doing%20meal%20prep%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20slight%20inconvenience.%20But%20we've%20gotten%20along%20very%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212a5cad7-ae57-4de5-afa3-5e9b52436ce3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWealth%20is%20more%20than%20money%3B%20it's%20the%20time%20you%20control%2C%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20has%20been%20able%20to%20devote%20more%20hours%20to%20the%20work%20she%20wants%20to%20do%20in%20the%20business%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20spend%20more%20focused%2C%20quality%20time%20with%20our%20daughter%20without%20distraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20this%20help%20also%20gives%20us%20leverage.%20The%20additional%20time%20devoted%20to%20our%20business%20provides%20the%20opportunity%20to%20increase%20our%20income%20more%20than%20we%20could%20save%20by%20trying%20to%20avoid%20hiring%20additional%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWealth%20is%20about%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20what's%20in%20your%20bank%20account%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20how%20much%20autonomy%20you%20have%3B%20how%20much%20you%20can%20choose%20what%20you%20do%20or%20don't%20do%20with%20the%20time%20you%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECould%20we%20save%20more%20money%20by%20doing%20everything%20ourselves%3F%20Perhaps%20we'd%20have%20a%20little%20more%20cash%20on%20hand%2C%20but%20we'd%20be%20extremely%20depleted%20in%20terms%20of%20time%20and%20energy.%20Could%20I%20have%20a%20higher%20net%20worth%20if%20I%20devoted%20%3Cem%3Eall%20%3C%2Fem%3Emy%20time%20to%20work%3F%20Of%20course%2C%20but%20my%20life%20would%20also%20be%20a%20lot%20smaller%20and%20emptier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%2C%20peace%2C%20energy%2C%20and%20health%20are%20all%20measures%20of%20wealth%2C%20alongside%20money.%20Arguably%2C%20those%20things%20are%20all%20more%20valuable%20than%20the%20dollars%20on%20my%20balance%20sheet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-house-manager-1200-month-worth-it-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762769101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690e3e467f37aa653f55a473%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-house-manager-1200-month-worth-it-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eric%20Roberge%20realized%20tasks%20around%20the%20house%20were%20taking%20away%20from%20his%20work%20and%20his%20family%20time.%20He%20hired%20a%20house%20manager%20who%20works%2010%20hours%20a%20week.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eric%20Roberge)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-house-manager-1200-month-worth-it-2025-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hamas%20hands%20over%20body%20of%20soldier%20killed%20in%202014%20Gaza%20war%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762768983000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-125221475%2Cimgsize-860577.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fhamas-hands-over-body-of-soldier-killed-in-2014-gaza-war%2Farticleshow%2F125221288.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F125221288.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EHamas%20has%20returned%20the%20remains%20of%20Israeli%20soldier%20Hadar%20Goldin%2C%20who%20died%20in%20Gaza%20in%202014.%20His%20body%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20Red%20Cross%20and%20met%20by%20Israeli%20troops.%20Goldin's%20family%20campaigned%20fo